         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... which 24 ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... not ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... inside ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... is to stay at home ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... not in front of ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">In one frame with <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408j"/>-<ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408n"/> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408p"/>-<ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408r"/>. The upper margin of the recto (lower of the recto) and the left part of the string hole space are preserved. Although this fragment is not edited by <bibl><title corresp="ref:ogihara2009"/></bibl>, I think that <hi>täṣne</hi> directly preceding a number (see also <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408j"/> a2) can also be taken as an indication that this fragment belongs to the Bhikṣuṇī-Prātimokṣasūtra. Therefore, it is provisionally assumed that it belongs to manuscript A 415-416, not to A 406-408.</note></p>
